# Tailwind CSS Guide

## Setup

```bash
npm install
npm run css        # Watch mode
npm run css:build  # Production build
```

## Usage

Apply Tailwind utility classes directly in templ components:

```
templ Button(label string) {
    <button class="px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700">
        { label }
    </button>
}
```

## Configuration

Edit `tailwind.config.js` to customize the design system. The `content` paths
are pre-configured to scan `.templ` and `.go` files in `internal/web/`.

## File Structure

```
static/css/
├── input.css      Tailwind directives (@tailwind base, components, utilities)
└── output.css     Generated CSS (do not edit)
```

## Custom Components

Use `@apply` in `input.css` for reusable component classes:

```css
@layer components {
    .btn-primary {
        @apply px-4 py-2 bg-blue-600 text-white rounded hover:bg-blue-700;
    }
}
```
